Bonjour,
J'ai le plaisir de vous transmettre l'information=20
ci dessous avec mes excuses en cas de r=E9ception multiple.

This is the first announcement of an event of the=20
European Regional Section of the International=20
Association for Statistical Computing (IASC-ERS):

Summer School on Compositional Data Analysis (CoDA)
7-11 July 2014
Girona, Spain

Compositions are vectors whose components show=20
the relative importance of some parts (in=20
percentages, ppm, ppb, or the like) of a whole.

Typical examples are: economy (income/expenditure=20
distribution), medicine (body composition: fat,=20
bone, muscle), food industry (food composition:=20
fat, sugar, =85), geochemistry and chemometrics=20
(chemical composition), ecology (abundance=20
different species), sociology (time-use surveys),=20
and genetics (genotype frequency). This hot topic=20
of research has nowadays a broad impact in these fields.

The goal of the IASC-ERS CoDA Summer School in=20
2014 is to learn the basic concepts on CoDA and=20
introduce its multivariate techniques (cluster=20
analysis, discriminant analysis, regression models, etc).

Statisticians and applied scientists of any=20
field, in particular engineering geologists,=20
geologists, economics, scientists, environmental=20
engineers, and bio&environmental scientists,=20
working in academic or industrial institutions,=20
are strongly encouraged to take the IASC-ERS=20
Summer School on CoDA. It is recommended that=20
attendants have already undergone some first=20
semester courses on statistics. Basic knowledge=20
about multivariate statistics may also be handy.
Due to the class room facilities at the UdG, the places are limited to 30.

Early registration is recommended (will open on=20
October 1st, 2013 at:=20
<http://www.compositionaldata.com//pages/codacourses/codacourse_form.html>w=
ww.compositionaldata.com//pages/codacourses/codacourse_form.html).

Further information at=20
<http://www.compositionaldata.com>www.compositionaldata.com=20
as well as in the list of forthcoming events on=20
the IASC website: <http://www.iasc-isi.org/node/41>www.iasc-isi.org/node/41

The CoDA IASC-ERS Summer School is organized by=20
the Research Group on Statistical MEthods in=20
resTRICted spaceS (METRICS) from the Computer=20
Science, Applied Mathematics and Statistics=20
Department of the University of Girona (UdG).

More information on the CoDA School is available=20
at:=20
<http://www.compositionaldata.com//pages/codacourses/Short_description_CoDA=
CourseUdG_IASC2014.pdf>www.compositionaldata.com//pages/codacourses/Short_d=
escription_CoDACourseUdG_IASC2014.pdf

We would be grateful if you could forward this=20
announcement to your students and colleagues.

Our best CoDa-regards,

J.A. Mart=EDn-Fern=E1ndez
(Organizer)
<mailto:josepantoni.martin@udg.edu>josepantoni.martin@udg.edu


